org.apache.flink.streaming.runtime.tasks

类 OperatorChain<OUT,OP extends StreamOperator<OUT>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.streaming.runtime.tasks.OperatorChain<OUT,OP>
  • 类型参数:
    OUT - The type of elements accepted by the chain, i.e., the input type of the chain's head operator.
    所有已实现的接口:
    StreamStatusMaintainer, StreamStatusProvider

    @Internal
public class OperatorChain<OUT,OP extends StreamOperator<OUT>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements StreamStatusMaintainer
    The OperatorChain contains all operators that are executed as one chain within a single StreamTask.

      • streamStatus

        private StreamStatus streamStatus
        Current status of the input stream of the operator chain. Watermarks explicitly generated by operators in the chain (i.e. timestamp assigner / watermark extractors), will be blocked and not forwarded if this value is StreamStatus.IDLE.

      • flushOutputs

        public void flushOutputs()
                  throws java.io.IOException
        This method should be called before finishing the record emission, to make sure any data that is still buffered will be sent. It also ensures that all data sending related exceptions are recognized.
        抛出:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown, if the buffered data cannot be pushed into the output streams.

      • releaseOutputs

        public void releaseOutputs()
        This method releases all resources of the record writer output. It stops the output flushing thread (if there is one) and releases all buffers currently held by the output serializers.

        This method should never fail.
